cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on resource scheduling in cloud data centers and proposes a simulator for evaluating different scheduling policies and algorithms.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper mentions load-balance and energy-efficiency scheduling, which are related to network and internet architecture.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the process of initializing cloud data centers and providing performance evaluation for various scheduling algorithms, which can be seen as a control problem.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper mentions adopting agile design patterns to assure flexibility and extensibility in the simulator's design.
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possible category as the paper focuses on performance evaluation of virtual machine allocation in cloud data centers.
